column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Cloudy , Heavy Rain , Light Wind Blowing Upstream
column14: FT2 wade 10m u/s gauge. Good quality mmnt. @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ Stage changing rapidly during field visit. Most likely due to heavy rains which subsided during the FV. Reset HG2 originally but shouldnt have due to changing stage. Reset again to match HG at 16:46. Used logged values for MGH. Mid-section

column12: Measurement condition : Ice; Clear , No Precipitation , Very Light Wind Swirling/Variable
column13: Open lead in gauge pool. Evidence of over-ice flow.
column14: Attempted an ice measurement approx 360m downstream but found multi-layers of water and ice. Instead, completed an FT2 wade at the open lead 5m u/s of the gauge. Confirmed border ice is frozen to bottom on near side (drilled through border ice and confirmed ground with ice probe), chopped surface ice on far bank and waded on top of anchor ice. Negative flow in one panel adjacent to edge (eddy). @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ HG2 is slushing, and not reset.  Mid-section
HG: 2.345 HG2: 2.086 Surge: 0.000  * The uncertainty value is equivalent to the surge value in eHSN.  Found (FD)
HG: 1.998 HG2: 1.990 Found (FD)

column12: Measurement condition : Ice; Clear , No Precipitation , Very Light Wind Swirling/Variable
column14: Measured approx 320m downstream, 5m downstream of large log jam on left bank. Right edge was 2.5m from the rigfht bank. Left edge was 5m from left bank. Previously attempted to measure at the two other winter measurement locations but ran into issues. Furthest downstream mmnt section had a layer of ice, layer of water and more ice. Transect near teh pedestrian bridge downstream of the gauge had very low effective depths. Low shift not entirely unexpected - suspect control change prior to Sept field visit (when we recorded a +140% shift). @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ Set HG averaging time 3 samples, sample eriod 5s. Tiered ice - suspect open lead had melted towards center of channel. Very thinice in middle(~2 cm thick). Did not require ice auger to punch a hole for DWL. Much thicker ice near bank. Mid-section

column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Smokey , No Precipitation , Very Light Wind Swirling/Variable
column14: Easy wade approx 30m upstream of gauge. Flow (at gauge) is mostly confined to left (nearside) bank. No obvious signs of scour - large positive shift possibly attributed to uncertainty/variability on the low end of the curve? Review curve in office. @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ Purge caused no change for CFB so reset. Suspect water (for winter DWL) will be closer to the gauge compared to last winter. Mid-section
HG: 1.992 HG2: 1.974 Surge: 0.010  * The uncertainty value is equivalent to the surge value in eHSN.  Found (FD)
